This year's Holocaust Remembrance Day is also the 75th anniversary of Auschwitz-Birkenau's liberation. We remember the 1.1 million lives lost at Auschwitz alone, & many more who suffered during the Holocaust. In honor of victims and survivors, we say: never forget; never again.

Gov. @GavinNewsom launches new state website with resources for those affected by wildfire and power outages. Site includes info on emergency response, recovery, health services, shelters/housing, & preparedness from local & state sources. Check it out: https://response.ca.gov/

@PGE4Me plans to shut off power in portions of Napa, Lake, and Sonoma counties today at 3pm. You can find more information, including affected addresses and locations for Community Resource Centers, at http://www.pgealerts.com/. We'll share more info as it becomes available. #PSPS

Please see below for more on @PGE4Me possible power shutoff this week. 1,895 customers in Lake, 9623 in Napa, 33,613 in Sonoma counties could be affected. Yolo, Colusa, & Solano have been removed. Link here with more info on possible impacted locations: http://bit.ly/2MWaZsQ

Proud to report that #AB744 was signed by @CAgovernor Gavin Newsom! #Telehealth is a vital piece to ensuring our rural communities have comprehensive access to medical care. Update: @PGE4Me is moving towards restoring power for counties in #AD4 affected by Public Safety Power Shutoff. Please note restoration won't be immediate as PG&E must inspect lines for safety before reenergizing, but inspection/repair process has begun. Stay tuned. #PSPS

We understand constituents have been experiencing difficulty getting through to @PGE4Me website; they have set up another site with essential information on the power shutoff event. Please see below for the latest information. #PSPS

As you may be readying for PG&E #PSPS outages in #AD4 tonight, please make sure to follow your local officials for more information in your area, and check out these tips to prepare for extended power outages. You can find the latest @PGE4Me, as well as at https://www.pgecurrents.com/2019/10/08/pge-will-proactively-turn-off-power-for-safety-to-nearly-800000-customers-across-northern-and-central-california-2/
Please see the below information for the locations that could be affected by tonight's Public Safety Power Shutoff @PGE4Me event. #PSPS #AD4

@PGE4Me confirms implementation of a Public Safety Power Shutoff as early as tonight. PG&E is notifying customers & will open several Community Resource Centers Oct. 9, 8 a.m. Centers will be open during daylight hours. More info below for before, during, and after a #PSPS event.

Condado de Napa ha establecido una Línea de Información Pública para el Centro de Operaciones de Emergencia. Llame al (707) 299-1501, y no al número del despacho de emergencia, para información acerca de los Apagones de Electricidad por Motivos de Seguridad Publica.

In anticipation of a Public Safety Power Shutoff (PSPS) by @PGE4Me, #NapaCounty has established a Public Information Line for the Emergency Operations Center. Please call (707) 299-1501, not the non-emergency dispatch number, for information regarding the PSPS.

Be prepared: @PGE4Me is considering initiating a Public Safety Power Shutoff in ~30 counties in anticipation of severe wind this week. This includes portions of Yolo, Colusa, Lake, Sonoma, Napa, and Solano. Check to see if your area could be affected here: https://www.pge.com/en_US/safety/emergency-preparedness/natural-disaster/wildfires/psps-service-impact-map.page
